{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:46:45.175Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official documentation and industry best practices for event-driven agent architectures, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"At-least-once vs exactly-once execution guarantees\""},{"type":"text","text":" refers to the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"two fundamental delivery semantics in distributed systems"},{"type":"text","text":" that determine how reliably events are processed — with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"at-least-once"},{"type":"text","text":" being the practical choice for most production systems (paired with idempotency) while "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exactly-once"},{"type":"text","text":" is theoretically impossible in large distributed systems and comes at extreme cost."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What They Are"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"At-Least-Once Delivery"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": The system guarantees that an operation will be executed "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"at least once"},{"type":"text","text":", with the possibility of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multiple executions"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Characteristic"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"r